"title": "7251: pillar of cloud and fire",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7251",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A physical manifestation of the presence of God among his people; a special form of theophany particularly associated with Israel being offered guidance on the exodus journey.</p>\n<h2>Functions of the pillar of cloud and fire</h2>\n<h3>To lead Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:21-Exod13:22\">EXO 13:21–13:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:36-Exod40:37\">EXO 40:36–40:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:17\">NUM 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:14\">NUM 14:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:12\">NEH 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:19\">NEH 9:19</a></p>\n<h3>To separate and protect Israel from the armies of Egypt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:19-Exod14:20\">EXO 14:19–14:20</a></strong> <em>This was just before the crossing of the Red Sea.</em></p>\n<h3>To represent God's presence, especially to Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:9\">EXO 33:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:5-Num12:6\">NUM 12:5–12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:15-Deut31:16\">DEU 31:15–31:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:7\">PSA 99:7</a></p>\n<h2>Effects of the pillar of cloud and fire</h2>\n<h3>It evoked worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:10\">EXO 33:10</a></p>\n<h3>It caused the nations to speak of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:14\">NUM 14:14</a></p>\n<h3>Experiencing the cloud did not guarantee acceptance by God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:1-1Cor10:5\">1CO 10:1–10:5</a></p>",
